condrift: Conditional drift in an admixture graph

We can consider an admixture graph like the following:

The graph topology together with the edge lengths and admixture proportions define a covariance matrix \(\Sigma\) where entry \(\sigma_{ij}\) is given by the \(F_2(i,j)\) statistics. This statistics we can both infer from the data and extract from a fitted graph. I havent fitted the graph here, so the covariance matrix shown below is completely arbitrary, but it is extracted from the graph.

            D       Alt         V        EU        EA        Af         C
D   1.0000000 0.0152725 0.0182725 0.1993401 0.1986401 0.2072725 0.3990725
Alt 0.0152725 1.0000000 0.0050000 0.2076276 0.2069276 0.2160000 0.4080000
V   0.0182725 0.0050000 1.0000000 0.2105476 0.2098476 0.2190000 0.4110000
EU  0.1993401 0.2076276 0.2105476 1.0000000 0.0013000 0.0080676 0.2196676
EA  0.1986401 0.2069276 0.2098476 0.0013000 1.0000000 0.0073676 0.2189676
Af  0.2072725 0.2160000 0.2190000 0.0080676 0.0073676 1.0000000 0.2200000
C   0.3990725 0.4080000 0.4110000 0.2196676 0.2189676 0.2200000 1.0000000

Since the graph gives us a multivariate Normal distribution of allele frequencies, we can relatively easy compute conditional probabilities, capturing what the correlation of two populations should be conditional on another, for example.

mu <- rep(0.5, length(graph$leaves))
names(mu) <- graph$leaves
model <- joint_drift_model(mu, Sigma)
plot_conditional_distribution <- function(a, b, x, f) {
  plot(condition(model, index = x, freq = f), indices = c(a, b)) +
    xlab(a) + ylab(b)
}
plot_conditional_distribution("D", "V", "Af", f = 0.01)

plot_conditional_distribution("D", "V", "Af", f = 0.3)

plot_conditional_distribution("D", "V", "Af", f = 0.7)

plot_conditional_distribution("D", "V", "Af", f = 0.9)

expected_F4 <- function(model, a, b, c, d) {
  # E[(a-b)(c-d)] = E[ac]-E[ad]-E[bc]+E[bd]
  # E[xy] = E[x]E[y] + Cov(x,y)
  Eac <- model$mu[a] * model$mu[c] + model$Sigma[a, c]
  Ead <- model$mu[a] * model$mu[d] + model$Sigma[a, d]
  Ebc <- model$mu[b] * model$mu[c] + model$Sigma[b, c]
  Ebd <- model$mu[b] * model$mu[d] + model$Sigma[b, d]
  as.vector(Eac - Ead - Ebc + Ebd)
}
conditional_expected_F4 <- function(model, a, b, c, d, x) {
  cond <- function(f) {
    conditional_model <- condition(model, index = x, freq = f)
    expected_F4(conditional_model, a, b, c, d)  
  }
  Vectorize(cond)
}
freqs <- seq(0, 1, length.out = 200)
cond_F4 <- conditional_expected_F4(model, "D", "V", "Af", "C", "EU")
plot(freqs, cond_F4(freqs), type = 'l', xlab = "EU allele freq", 
     ylab = quote(F[4](D, V, Af, C)))

cond_F4 <- conditional_expected_F4(model, "D", "V", "EA", "C", "Af")
plot(freqs, cond_F4(freqs), type = 'l', xlab = "Af allele freq", 
     ylab = quote(F[4](D, V, EA, C)))

cond_F4 <- conditional_expected_F4(model, "EU", "EA", "V", "C", "Af")
plot(freqs, cond_F4(freqs), type = 'l', xlab = "Af allele freq", 
     ylab = quote(F[4](EU, EA, V, C)))
